episodes.name: Goat Tell It on the Mountain
episodes.overview: The buyers try to get away from it all, heading out to Lake Arrowhead, where Ivy puts economies of scale to the test. Justin almost hits the bullseye on his locker, while Darrell and Chad's fortunes are found on the farm.

episodes.name: Ivy: The Pro-fession-ale
episodes.overview: Dave brings his mentor with him to Rancho Cucamonga, Calif., but has little to show for it; Brandi and Jarrod go all in on a hunch; Kenny tries to downsize his strategy; Ivy shows a skeptical Emily how he pulls a win out of a locker.

episodes.name: Mary's RE-finds
episodes.overview: Nine stories of treasures in the Koreatown neighborhood of Los Angeles; the Vegas Ladies discover that one of them has Texas flair; Kenny lucks out looking for lady stuff; Mary gets the spring back in her step.

episodes.name: Crickets And Wickets
episodes.overview: Rene brings Gunther along to West Covina, Calif., for moral support, but gets annoyed when the older German will not take sides; Darrell stumbles over a potential diamond in the rough; Brandi and Jarrod discover a different national pastime.

episodes.name: Quality Bro Chime
episodes.overview: During "Bring Your Brother to Work Day" in Thousand Oaks, Calif., Justin sinks his money into a unit with an interesting pair; Dave pushes Mary to the breaking point; Kenny makes a nice profit piece by piece.

episodes.name: And Mary Ran Away With the Spoon
episodes.overview: In Huntington Beach, Calif., Darrell's insider information amplifies his investment considerably; Mary's find cooks up some oversized accoutrements; Kenny takes advantage of others' missteps to grab a unit.

episodes.name: Indiana Ivy and the Temple of Phlegm
episodes.overview: Darrell is at risk of losing the title of "The King of Montebello"; Brandi and Jarrod find their way back to the auction with the help of some pocket tech; Casey bails herself out despite being confined with an infectious German.

episodes.name: Tour de Van Nuys
episodes.overview: Mary needs help managing a tiny parking lot in Van Nuys, Calif.; Ivy goes on the prowl for a bike; Dave scores a therapeutic locker; Justin tries to show the rest of the buyers how to make the most out of a unit.

episodes.name: Bo-ZAK That Whip!
episodes.overview: It's "prison" hugs all around in the city of Orange. Brandi and Jarrod bring an old friend to do all the heavy lifting. Ivy finds his fun in little things. Amidst all the water damage, Mary discovers where her bread is really buttered. Shana and Edwina crack themselves up with some snappy accessories.

episodes.name: We Don't Use the 'S' Word Around Here
episodes.overview: Rolling into Buena Park with their crew, Brandi and Jarrod pick up what may be the best of the worst. Kenny and his cousin glide through a locker that's only half decent. Ivy comes to the auction dressed to kill and Mary tries to turn up the volume.

episodes.name: The Jenny, the Baker, the Prosthetics Maker
episodes.overview: Jarrod takes Brandi to an auction on her birthday; Darrell tries to find another "All Ten" locker; Rene stands his ground to protect his honor; Mary brings in her pal from Texas to put her California counterparts in their place.

episodes.name: Weekend at Barry's
episodes.overview: Kenny feels nostalgic in Koreatown, so he brings along an old friend, which may or may not be a good idea; Brandi and Jarrod sweeten their profit in an unexpected way; Ivy tolerates the big city in an effort to find some name-brand goodies.

episodes.name: A Sale of Two Cities
episodes.overview: Emily brings her mother along; Darrell wastes no time finding an advantage; Ivy and Ivy Jr. clean up with their locker; Kenny gets some advice from a music legend; Shana and Edwina settle for thrifting what's in front of them.

episodes.name: They Shoe Horses, Don't They
episodes.overview: In Hesperia, Calif., Mary's transportation troubles lead to her teaming up with Kenny and taking him out to pasture; Darrell shows the next generation of Gambler how it's done; the Vegas Ladies' mid-century style lets them write their own ticket.

episodes.name: Talkin’ In Cody
episodes.overview: Emily brings along her cowboy husband to Moreno Valley; Ivy is displeased at Mary’s fraternization with the auctioneer and takes it out on her later; and Kenny looks for anything in his locker that can wash off that storage scent.

episodes.name: Om Sweet Om
episodes.overview: The Vegas Ladies show up in Bourgie Brea; Mary decides to deal with her storage stress by introducing a bit of yoga into her routine; and Ivy and Dave go head-to-head on a giant pair of sister lockers, but Dave chooses to sit out the rest of the time.

episodes.name: Grandma’s Havoc
episodes.overview: In Victorville, Ivy takes it easy, letting Ivy, Jr. run the operation. Kenny feels run down and his lack of focus lands him a locker, but there is a pleasant surprise in the end. Mary, Shana, and Edwina cannot seem to make anything stick, so they decide to embrace it, doing what they do best.

episodes.name: Cloudy with a Chance of Profit
episodes.overview: It is a momentous occasion in Van Nuys for Darrell, and he has a completely groovy time with it. Ivy starts his day off with an unwelcome bang. Brandi and Jarrod are left wondering whether their unit will bring clear skies or clouds ahead.

episodes.name: Let's Give 'Em Something to Tonka About
episodes.overview: Dave counts on his competition being unwilling to buy a big locker they need to move; Ivy and Ivy Jr. find their day somewhat therapeutic; Mary finally finds a tiny treasure to take home; Rene stands his ground to protect his honor.

episodes.name: Fowl Play
episodes.overview: Dave sees his profits grow, among other things, in Torrance, Calif.; Mary finds clothes that don't fit her, which turns out to be a good thing; Kenny takes a chance at being an early bird, but winds up looking more like a dodo.

episodes.name: What Came First: The Chicken or the Auction?
episodes.overview: Overwhelmed by the sheer number of units up for auction in Rialto, Calif., Mary and Ivy wager that each can better predict final locker prices than the other; Dave's locker resembles a chop shop; Rene and Tatianna score vintage sporting goods.

episodes.name: The Wind Beneath My Bids
episodes.overview: Winds in excess of 30 mph batter Desert Hot Springs, Calif., and the buyers do their best to keep standing; Rene and Gunther dust off an old locker; Brandi and Jarrod's unit takes a turn and ends up lapping the competition; Kenny steps up his game.

episodes.name: Not All That Glitters Is Gourd
episodes.overview: Back in the city of Orange, Calif., the Vegas Ladies arrive in vintage style, though not everyone agrees; Casey finds the chutzpah to pick up a good unit; Darrell tries to peddle his wares to Emily, but settles for a decent locker.

episodes.name: Mistress of the Snark
episodes.overview: In Stanton, Calif., Ivy thinks he's a comic, but the gizmo in his locker is no joke; Brandi and Jarrod make sure that what they find in their unit doesn't stay there; Kenny's vintage entertainment lands him an excuse to meet a cult TV host.

episodes.name: Nowhere to Formaldehyde
episodes.overview: Emily's husband, Cody, misses a bid and stirs up trouble; Brandi and Jarrod put their faith in the cowboy and end up facing their mortality; the Vegas Ladies struggle to be seen; Ivy revisits some of his glory days.

episodes.name: Drama in the LBC
episodes.overview: The buyers manage to make a charitable contribution in the neighborhood of North Long Beach; Darrell and Dave wager on who got the better sister locker; Brandi and Jarrod spend way too much, but see their treasure soar.

episodes.name: Santanas Are Coming to Town
episodes.overview: Recently separated, Brandi and Jarrod find themselves at the same auction, and tensions flare; she gets the Laura treatment, and he regresses to his childhood self; Ivy schools Ivy Jr., who needs to find his footing.

episodes.name: Bits and Pizzas
episodes.overview: The King of Montebello can't wait to see what he can drum up this time around; Rene sniffs out a great locker, stepping over the competition to get it; Kenny does his best to fire up his profits; Brandi can't see the potential in the units.

episodes.name: Lets Make a Dill!
episodes.overview: Back in Montebello, Brandi and her buddy set the wayback machine and discover a roaring good time; Darrell makes the most of the little he's got; Kenny fills his piggy bank, while courting an unfamiliar pastime.

episodes.name: Mirro, Mirro, on the Floor
episodes.overview: Dan and Laura hope for better units and better buyers; Rene tries to capitalize on warehouse sales and scoots away with a deal; Jarrod treats himself to a spa day; Darrell reflects on what it means to buy lockers full of antiques.

episodes.name: Rules #1
episodes.overview: Ivy brings his son to Moreno Valley, where good things always happen, and leaves with yo-yo's of an unexpected kind. Rene and Casey discover that their shoes are more "air" and less "Jordan." Kenny tries to level up his locker, while Lisa learns to look beyond the trash.

episodes.name: Queen-baya!
episodes.overview: The buyers get wind of some interesting units in Santa Clarita; Ivy and Isaiah choose quantity over quality; Brandi gets fancy sneaking a unit from everyone else; Kenny finds himself searching for his soul sister.

episodes.name: Game of Groans: Whittier Is Coming
episodes.overview: Kenny tries to reclaim the title of "King of Whittier" but has trouble amassing any shillings. Ivy & Ivy brave the cold to find their fortunes. Lisa finally graduates to full-fledged buyer, finding an unlikely mentor along the way.

episodes.name: Breaking Bread
episodes.overview: Kenny treats Perris, CA like a European vacation, picking up girls along the way. Jarrod's crappy locker doesn't offer him any protection. Rene's tools end up being older than he expects.

episodes.name: Dr. D and the Mystery Machines
episodes.overview: Less is mostly more in Brea; Rene swings for the fences on a costly gamble; Brandi has to dig through trash but really puts her heart into it nonetheless; Ivy and Pops clear up confusion over a massive mysterious mechanism.

episodes.name: A Plane Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest
episodes.overview: The gang is on final approach in Riverside; Darrell listens to his sports sense, and it pays off; Ivy and Ivy get distracted by a decoy but manage to find the bills in the end; Brandi tries to teach Danielle a lesson about the true meaning of trash.

episodes.name: Older and Weiss-er
episodes.overview: Everything seems like business as usual in West Covina, Calif., until a crazy-looking vintage Mercury Zephyr pulls up, revealing an old friend; Darrell and his buddy stumble over the ultimate sketch artist; Ivy and his son can't seem to pick a lane.

episodes.name: Let My Lockers Go
episodes.overview: Ivy confuses profit with prophet but still manages to climb his way to success; Kenny tries to honor the history of San Bernardino, Calif., recording a win along the way; Brandi shows her literary prowess volume by volume.

episodes.name: Fears Of A Clown
episodes.overview: It's a regular father and son shootout in Victorville, as Ivy and Pops try to prove who among them is the most profitable. Brandi's secret weapon lands her more than she bargained for but luckily, Kenny is there to brighten her day.

episodes.name: Stanton And Redeliver
episodes.overview: A confident Kenny has a 3-step plan for success in Stanton. Darrell helps Kimber find winning items for her new boutique. Rene brings Casey, who needs a distraction. And Laura takes lead as auctioneer, while Dan... holds the clipboard.

episodes.name: The Old Man and the Spree
episodes.overview: Kenny's fear of sharks inspires a controversial wardrobe choice in Oceanside. Rene brings his "bargain army" along to try and intimidate the competition, while he gets his slice of the loot. Darrell won't take 'no' for an answer, moving full steam ahead.

episodes.name: She Bidded Me With Science!
episodes.overview: Lisa decides to be fact-based in Placentia, inadvertently complicating international relations. Ivy and his son conjure up a locker with some mysterious sports equipment. Rene won't be taken advantage of and it allows him to record a nice win.

episodes.name: Not So Easy Rider
episodes.overview: Barry rolls up to Riverside with his own masked bidder, and the two develop a winning strategy. Brandi and Danielle's mystery balls take them to South America...sort of. Rene needs a cleanse after going through his risqu room.

episodes.name: Pretty Fly...For A Locker!
episodes.overview: San Bernardino brings out the warrior in Ivy, who goes up against an upstart buyer. Kenny has his eye on a locker that leaves him needing a massage; while Lisa angles for a smaller unit but ends up with the catch of the day.

episodes.name: High Tea And Boxed Whine
episodes.overview: Brandi lets Danielle lead the way in Santa Ana. Rene takes a gamble on the packaging.

episodes.name: She Sure Has A Type
episodes.overview: In Lancaster, it's not the other buyers but rather a small animal that catches Lisa off guard, though she does snag a new type of prize. Ivy and Isaiah barrel their way through a unit, leaving them in need of a drink, while Darrell keeps getting stuck behind an old lady.

episodes.name: The Devil Buys Used Prada
episodes.overview: Kenny tries bribing the other team in Canyon Country; Isaiah and Ivy makes the most of their lot; Brandi faces the powers of darkness.

episodes.name: Spidey Cents
episodes.overview: Brandi wakes up on the wrong side of the bed but feels much better after picking up a locker in Placentia; Rene goes to the office to quickly flip his money; Kenny struggles just to get through his unit, which seems to have it in for him.

episodes.name: Another One Bites The Dusty
episodes.overview: Barry arrives code 3 to Stanton, where he takes on a new disciple. Lisa gets clinical with her find, forcing her to take a closer look. The new guy pays heavily for a unit, but seems to know what he's doing, while Brandi and Rene struggle to stay in the game.

episodes.name: Come And Knock On Our Locker
episodes.overview: Brandi wakes up on the wrong side of the bed but makes the best of it in Fullerton. Meanwhile, Ivy snipes one locker and grabs a second, knocking out the competition. and Kenny finds something precious.

episodes.name: You Can Lead A Horse To A Locker, But You Can't Make Him Bid
episodes.overview: It's just another Riverside auction, until Barry and Kenny show up in their alternative fuel vehicle. Lisa does her best to break the curse of the bad locker and Ivy finds some curious denominations.

episodes.name: Piles To Go Before I Keep
episodes.overview: Laura takes the reigns alone in Fullerton and proceeds to outsell Dan; Brandi gets assaulted by her locker but ultimately drives home a winner; Rene postpones a day date in favor of a work date; Darrell stumbles across and unexpected collection.

episodes.name: In Pain In The Membrane
episodes.overview: In Victorville, a friendly duel runs Dusty up, but his vinyl might save him; Ivy's locker shines some light on the business; Lisa learns that she needs her locker about as much as she needs a hole in her head.

episodes.name: How The West Covina Was Won
episodes.overview: In West Covina, Lisa is so busy looking back that she makes the worst auction mistake; Rene finds a bargain and really makes the most of it; Ivy unfolds his way to a profit and unloads some stuff onto Lisa.

episodes.name: King Of Orange... Chicken
episodes.overview: Rene shows up in Orange, declaring himself the King, while Dusty isn't quite ready to concede the title; Kenny accidentally re-invents the wheel; Lisa sees things from a slightly different perspective.

episodes.name: Lego My Locker
episodes.overview: The units are packed full in Stanton, as Darrell has to deal with Kimber's eyes on a competitor. Ivy brings a full truck, hoping for a second haul. Dusty unpacks what could be the ultimate assistant, while Rene's hunch serves him well, putting together one of his greatest profits.

episodes.name: Reign or Shine
episodes.overview: It's an uncharacteristically wet day in Montebello and King Darrell is on a mission to defend his throne, while Rene and Casey signal their intentions to undermine his plans. Kenny gets entirely bowled over by his locker. And Lisa manages to rope herself something decent.

episodes.name: The King of Montebowl-o
episodes.overview: Barry shows up to the auction ready to learn, bringing along a present for a certain hustler. Brandi and Bozek get a firm grip on a smaller unit that raises their spirits. Ivy treats his son to a birthday locker, but it's The King himself that outdoes everyone with a rare find.

episodes.name: Here Comes the Calvin-ry!
episodes.overview: Lisa dons her cowboy garb and brings her money sock to Riverside. Rene sinks his teeth into an unassuming unit.

episodes.name: Zip Tie Lies
episodes.overview: Rene and Casey roll the dice on some sealed totes in San Bernardino. Kenny stumbles over some odd-looking car parts.

episodes.name: Children of the Cornbread
episodes.overview: Ivy is on the warpath in Lancaster and doing his best to intimidate the other buyers. Brandi lets Bozek decide which locker they buy.

episodes.name: Proxy Moxie
episodes.overview: Barry utilizes a little-known tactic to snatch up a locker. Brandi shops in the bargain basement but puts on quite a show.

episodes.name: Two for the Price of Dust
episodes.overview: The big guns come out in Riverside, but Rene isn't having any of it. Darrell presses his luck with a smaller locker and makes a neat profit. Dusty finds that once he gets going, it's hard to stop, so he just keeps re-loading.

episodes.name: It's a Safe Time to Get Lit!
episodes.overview: Lisa has her own take on a beach day, as she heads to Huntington Beach. Darrell spends the right amount of time going through his locker. Kenny rides a recent string of luck right into his unit, while Rene puts his bankroll up against a pair of safes.

episodes.name: All Hail, King Brandi: The Rule-her of West Covina
episodes.overview: In West Covina, Brandi makes a serious land grab and it pays off handsomely. Rene can't resist the mystery of a good safe. Kenny can't seem to satisfy his hunger, while Barry takes an opportunity to poach from the competition.

episodes.name: YOLO Bolo!
episodes.overview: Rene goes big; Ivy scores a packed locker and stumbles across an antique of unusual origin; Darrell grabs a smaller unit but finds that good things do, indeed, come in petite packages sometimes.

episodes.name: Stanton in the Place Where You Work
episodes.overview: Rene has lukewarm results bobbin' for profits in Stanton. Dusty finds a hoard of quality equipment, inking himself a decent payday. Looking for treasure, Brandi does end up with the green... just not in the way she expected.

episodes.name: Perm-anently Fulle
episodes.overview: All the whales are coming to the big auction in Fullerton... or at least, that's what Barry hears as he takes Dusty under his wing to see what kind of profit he can style. Rene has some dainty discoveries, while Darrell's tool locker is quite eye-opening.

episodes.name: I Love Lupe!
episodes.overview: The women outnumber the men in Rosamond, as Dusty and his girlfriend discover a stockpile of vintage TV memorabilia. Brandi enlists the help of both Danielle and Lisa to dig for gold, and what they find gives them pause. Kenny stumbles over what appears to be an exotic music box.

episodes.name: Etrog, Lupe?
episodes.overview: Lancaster is Ivy's honeypot, so everyone had better watch out or they might get stung. Lisa plans to use the right side of her brain when selecting lockers...or is it the left? While Dusty and "Tollbooth Lupe" do a mitzvah.

episodes.name: Vending, Vidi, Vici!
episodes.overview: The buyers head out to Palm Springs, in search of higher end goods. Kenny tries to amp up the profit on an otherwise unimpressive unit. Rene sees quick potential where others don't and puts his pocket change into it. Brandi and Bozek try to keep their gains from squirming away.

episodes.name: Parasol Pals
episodes.overview: The sun is beating down in Oceanside, bringing out all the parasols. Dusty and Lupe steal a no-brainer locker and it pays off handsomely. Darrell taxes himself and it almost puts him in storage jail. Brandi and Lisa find their true identities and ultimately "re-cover" their investment.

episodes.name: The Way of the Gam Gam
episodes.overview: While in Santa Ana, Lisa channels her grandmother, in trying to turn a profit. Brandi is dealing with the most frustrating day ever. Darrell tries to make a meal out of a snack-sized locker and Kenny learns to prep himself for true stealthiness.

episodes.name: Four Bidders and a Funeral
episodes.overview: Lisa comes to Montebello with a clear mind, intent on letting the lockers speak to her. Ivy lets his son navigate his way to a unit which turns out not to be completely vacant. Kenny is absolutely appalled by what he finds abandoned in his unit.

episodes.name: Manifest Chastity
episodes.overview: Brandi is determined to actually win a locker for once in Santa Ana and has to show restraint to do it. Rene spots a stack of items in a locker that speaks to him. Kenny puts his needs out to the universe, while Barry struggles to stay in the game.

episodes.name: We Fun-did It!
episodes.overview: Ivy drags Isaiah to Victorville as punishment for getting C's on his report card. Kenny wants to furnish his new house, but there are eight reasons standing in his way. And not to be cheesy, but Lisa learns a lot.

episodes.name: San Brandi-Dino!
episodes.overview: Brandi is fired up about expanding her brand in San Bernardino. Rene is positive that everyone is out to get him. Dusty tackles a locker dustier than him. Kenny... well he's just a mess.

episodes.name: Your PawPaw Loves You!
episodes.overview: Lisa returns to Moreno Valley, where it all started, and gets nostalgic with her locker. Kenny welcomes a new granddaughter to the clan and would love to find an appropriate unit. Dusty and Lupe put a little elbow grease into their purchase.

episodes.name: Strings & Beans
episodes.overview: Ivy takes on a supervisory role in Stanton and it leads him to a bit of Slavic success. Brandi tries to help Danielle outfit her new apartment. Lisa gambles on a painting.

episodes.name: Pin Up or Shut Up
episodes.overview: Dusty and Lupe pedal their way to an auction in Fullerton, but end up needing the truck. Darrell pins his hopes on a small locker for which he overpaid. Rene makes the most of "the Honeymoon unit" and things get a bit racy.

episodes.name: Rock, Paper, Winner
episodes.overview: Back in Montebello, Gunter comes along to help Rene, who won't give him the time of day; Darrell tries to make Kimber his queen; Ivy and his boys Rochambeau their way to solid showing.

episodes.name: Does a Bear Bid in the Woods?
episodes.overview: Kenny makes his way out to the mountains, watching out for cougars the whole time; Lisa scores on a small sister locker, but it's Brandi who gets the nomination for buyer of the week.

episodes.name: California Knows How to Pottery
episodes.overview: Ivy kidnaps Pops and takes him to Rosamond, where they deftly score a fine locker; Kenny sets out to brighten everyone's day and his clowning around has him seeing stars; Lisa proves she has a friend... for now.

episodes.name: If Ya Got It, Flaut It
episodes.overview: Kenny happens upon a familiar vehicle and follows it all the way to Lancaster for an auction; Rene tries to find new luck, after losing in Vegas; Lisa tries to make up for last time; the Calvins look to a higher power for their profit.

episodes.name: Every Party Needs a Pooper
episodes.overview: Laura's on her own in Moreno Valley, and she's anything but discreet about the reasons; Brandi cooks up a nice profit; Rene's doll locker yields a couple surprises, while Ivy dabbles with a bit of the supernatural.

episodes.name: We Were Promised Fun
episodes.overview: Ivy ropes his kids into a beach day in Victorville and they make the best of it; Brandi tries to erase bad camping memories with a good locker; despite Rene giving him a hard time for his choices, Kenny manages to scrape out a decent return.

episodes.name: Five Cards But No Stud
episodes.overview: Rene shows up to West Covina feeling very nostalgic; Kenny zeroes in a tricycle locker and deals with what's inside; the Calvins just try to have a fun day, while Barry can't understand the general lack of professionalism among his peers.

episodes.name: Why Did the Chicken Cross the Road? Don't Ask Brandi
episodes.overview: Ivy and Pops shop for bags in Fullerton but end up with containers; Darrell and Kimber go all in on a toy locker, while Brandi covers her costs in an otherwise unassuming household unit.
